<HEAD>Tremor Shakes Anchorage, Alaska, Area</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A light earthquake shook Alaska's Anchorage
area early Sunday, the U.S. Geological Survey reported.
   The tremor was reported at a preliminary magnitude of 4.0 on the
Richter scale and was centered about 20 miles north of Anchorage,
said survey spokesman Don Finley.
   Geological Survey earthquake monitors in Golden, Colo., showed
that the tremor occurred at 1:11 a.m. Alaska daylight time, or 5:11
a.m. EDT, he said. The quake was reported felt in Anchorage, Palmer
and Eagle River.
   There were no immediate reports of damage, Finley said.
