<FIRST>r a AM-HotelSickness     04-30 0177</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Hotel Sickness,0182</SECOND>
<HEAD>Five Hospitalized After Falling Ill at Hotel</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LOS ANGELES (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   An unexplained illness hospitalized five
people and sickened dozens of others after a seminar luncheon at a
hotel Sunday.
   Paramedics were called to the Century Plaza Hotel about 1:15
p.m., said Fire Department spokesman Greg Acevedo.
   ``We had a group of about 20 or 30 people who came down with
nausea and vomiting'' after the halibut luncheon, but it was
unclear if the cause was food poisoning, said Katie Meyer, a
spokeswoman for the plush hotel.
   ``A doctor who was here with the group said it appeared to be a
chemical reaction,'' she said.
   However, all items offered at lunch were removed from the hotel
menu as a precaution, she said.
   Five women were taken to Beverly Hills Medical Center, where
they were being examined and were listed in stable condition Sunday
afternoon, authorities said.
   The stricken were among 400 people at the luncheon, which was
part of the Los Angeles Radiological Society's 14th annual spring
diagnostic ultra-sound conference, Ms. Meyer said.
</TEXT>
